
#### What does ARP stand for? ####

- Address Resolution Protocol.

#### What is the purpose of ARP? ####

- To map MAC Addresses to IP Addresses for communication in Layer 2 switch networks.

#### How are ARP Requests done? ####

- Broadcasts to the whole network.
    -i.e, 192.168.2.1 wants to communicate with 192.168.2.2 but doesn't know the IP it would send out a whole has tell xxx.xxx.xxx.xxx
- Once a device finds the MAC Address for a new device it will store it in an ARP Cache.
    - ARP Caches are on a timer and are not forever.

### You can check your ARP Tables with the following commands ###

- WINDOWS: arp -a
- LINUX: arp

#### SUMMARY ####
- ARP Stands for Address Resolution Protocol
- ARP is used to discover devices inside of a local network
- ARP is used by sending out a broadcast asking for information to all devices on the LAN.
